	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-06-19T03:35:46">McColl's Retail Group plc is a United Kingdom-based retailer. The Company, through its stores, provides a range of essential everyday products and services across the United Kingdom. It operates in the segment of operation of convenience and newsagent stores. Its product range includes milk, meals, groceries, fruit and vegetables, sandwiches, newspapers and chilled food, among others. The Company has a network of around 1,315 convenience stores and newsagents. It operates approximately 799 McColl's convenience stores and around 516 newsagents branded Martin's and, in Scotland, RS McColl. Some of the Company's stores also offer beers, wines and spirits. The Company operates around 451 post offices across the United Kingdom. It offers a Plus card loyalty scheme to customers enabling them to access the offers available at its stores. It also offers various others services, such as lottery tickets, bill payment, cash machines, and Internet collection and return points.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2015-09-15T08:19:02">BRIEF: For the 26 weeks ended 31 May 2015, McColl's Retail Group PLC revenues increased 3% to L459.3M. Net income totaled L5.9M vs. loss of L3.6M. Revenues reflect an increase in demand for the Company's products and services due to favorable market conditions. Net Income reflects Net Financing Income/Expense decrease of 82% to L1.4M (expense),  Administrative expenses decrease of 3% to L112.8M (expense).</Text>
	</TextInfo>
